This section provides an overview of how to install Gluster Storage
Software Appliance.

To install Gluster Storage Software Appliance, perform the following
steps:

1.  Check the
http://www.gluster.org/community/documentation/index.php/Gluster_3.2:Gluster_Storage_Software_Appliance_License[Gluster
Storage Software Appliance License].
2.  Verify that your system matches the minimum system requirements. For
more information, refer to
http://www.gluster.org/community/documentation/index.php/Gluster_3.2:_Checking_Gluster_Storage_Software_Appliance_Minimum_Requirements[Checking
Gluster Virtual Storage Appliance Minimum Requirements].
3.  Complete the installation procedure. For more information, refer to
http://www.gluster.org/community/documentation/index.php/Gluster_3.2:_Installing_the_Gluster_Storage_Software_Appliance[Installing
the Gluster Storage Software Appliance].

*Note:* If you wish to install using USB stick, refer to
http://www.gluster.org/community/documentation/index.php/Gluster_3.2:_Downloading_and_Preparing_Installation_Media[Downloading
and Preparing Installation Media].

